		{
			"title": "总体经济增长",
			"body": "<p>Fears about China’s economy are shaking global markets and capital is leaving the country at an unprecedented pace.</p>\n<p>Investors are eager for clues about whether slides in China’s equity market and currency depreciation at the start of this year were a sign of acute distress in the real economy, or whether policymakers can engineer a gradual slowdown that avoids financial crisis and social instability.</p>",
			"nowcast": null,
			"group": "gdp",
			"charturl": null,
			"indexcard": true,
			"big-number": null,
			"bignum-heading": "QQ YYYY growth",
			"bignum-units": "%",
			"bignum-name": "CN real GDP",
			"arrow-direction": null,
			"annual-change": null,
			"annual-heading": "GDP per capita",
			"annual-name": "CN GDP cap",
			"short-change": null,
