		{
			"title": "增长来源",
			"body": "<p>The task of “rebalancing” the Chinese economy weighs heavily on policymakers’ minds. The government is attempting to steer the economy away from investment- and export-led growth, to growth based on domestic consumption. However, it is proving difficult to convince Chinese households to save less and spend more.</p>\n<p>A full rebalancing will require economic restructuring. This includes trimming down or getting rid of state-owned enterprises in overcapacity sectors such as coal mining and steel processing where profits have been dropping.</p>",
			"nowcast": null,
			"group": "sources",
			"charturl": null,
			"indexcard": true,
